<p><cc><u><b>CARD FOR JANE/ PART ONE/ WHICH SCHOOLS ARE OPEN</b></u></cc></p>
<p><cc> - Most primary schools in England will return today, but in London and some surrounding areas they will not open for most pupils until 18 January. </cc></p>
<p><cc></cc></p>
<p><cc>- Secondary schools in England will stagger their return with pupils taking exams in 2021 starting on 11 January, and other year groups returning in person on 18 January.</cc></p>
<p><cc></cc></p>
<p><cc> - In Scotland, the Christmas holidays have been extended to 11 January, and the following week will be online learning only. A full return to face-to-face learning is planned for 18 January.</cc></p>
<p><cc></cc></p>
<p><cc> - In Wales, local councils have been told they can be "flexible" with when they open.</cc></p>
<p><cc></cc></p>
<p><cc> - In Northern Ireland, primary school pupils will be taught online until 11 January. </cc></p>
<p></p>
